			<p>Look awesome! <img src='http://www.hookedonheat.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif' alt=':D' class='wp-smiley' /> How do you roll them out without the potato stuffing leaking out?! It always does when I roll them out!</p>
<p><em>Hi Shub! The trich here is to not overload them with the filling. The standard rule of  thunb I often use is this: for 1 tbsp of filling, I make sure the dough is rolled out to atleast a 3-4 inch circle. This way, when the filiing is placed in the centre, you&#8217;ll have enough of dough spaced on the sides to bring it in and close. Hope this helps!</em></p>
		</li>
		
		
		
	
